\title{a [bijective](jms-00KR) enumeration of the integers}
\date{2024-01-29}
\author{jonmsterling}
\contributor{marcelofiore}
\taxon{example}
\import{jms-00JB}

\p{We can define a bijective enumeration of the integers by “zigzagging” between the positive and the negative following the pattern\prn{0, -1, 1,-2,2,-3,3,\ldots}:}

##{
 \begin{aligned}
  e&\colon \mathbb{N}\twoheadrightarrow \mathbb{Z}\\
  e\prn{i} &=
  \begin{cases}
   0 &\text{when } i=0\\
   i\div 2 &\text{when } i > 0 \land 2\mid i\\
   -\prn{i+1}\div 2 &\text{when } i > 0 \land \lnot\prn{2\mid i}
  \end{cases}
 \end{aligned}
}